column16: 'Phenotype': 'The mutant plants are hypersensitive to both FRc and Rc light treatments in hypocotyl elongation and exhibits a small reciprocal enlargement in cotyledon area
column33: 'Phenotype': 'fkgp-1 mutants have about 40 times more L-fucose than wild type Arabidopsis plants
column34: but the levels of other monosaccharides do not appear to differ significantly in the mutants. No obvious phenotypic abnormalities were observed in the fkgp-1 mutants
column35: nor were any differences in the sugar composition of cell wall polysaccharides detected.'
column59: 'Phenotype': 'Resistant to exogenous ABA. Seeds contained lower amounts of endogenous ABA than wildtype.'
column75: 'Phenotype': 'The homozygous progeny is indistinguishable from wild-type plants during vegetative growth but showed several morphological alterations after bolting. column83: 'Phenotype': 'Decreased germination on high concentrations of glucose and sorbitol.'
column91: 'Phenotype': 'rgp1-1 mutants have significantly lower levels of UDP-L-arabinose mutase activity compared to wild-type plants and significantly lower levels of arabinose in their cell walls.'
column99: 'Phenotype': 'The triple homozygous progeny has low viability
column101: and all plants died before shoot emergence.'
column117: 'Phenotype': 'Significantly smaller when grown in the presence of methyl methanosulfonate (MMS) with root growth.  Normal growth under standard growth conditions.'
column125: 'Phenotype': 'The skor-1 mutant is sensitive to toxic cations in addition to K+ depletion.'
column157: 'Phenotype': 'Plants cold-shocked for 6h have an increased starch content compared to wildtype.'
column165: 'Phenotype': 'Mutant seeds grown on medium supplemented with non-phosphorylated synthetic 1-deoxy-D-xylulose (DX) develop green leaves.'
